15 WHEREAS, Children's Healthcare of Atlanta made history on September 29 when it moved
16 202 patients using 65 ambulances from Egleston Hospital to the new Arthur M. Blank
17 Hospital in fewer than 12 hours, representing one of the largest single-day pediatric hospital
18 moves in the country; and
19 WHEREAS, Children's Healthcare of Atlanta has been ranked as a top pediatric hospital by
20 U.S. News & World Report for 21 years, with eight specialties ranked in the top 20 and one
21 specialty ranked in the top 10, exemplifying its commitment to excellence in pediatric
22 healthcare.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
24 recognize and commend Children's Healthcare of Atlanta for its outstanding contributions
25 to pediatric healthcare in Georgia and celebrate the opening of the Arthur M. Blank Hospital,
26 a groundbreaking addition to our state that will provide life changing care to children and
27 families for generations to come.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
29 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Children's
30 Healthcare of Atlanta.
